  "text": "QS signals have already been identified among N-acyl homoserine lactones (AHLs) which are a family of QS signals has been identified in many Gram-negative bacteria such as Proteobacteria. AHL mediated quorum sensing regulates the expression of many genes responsible for biofilm formation, bioluminescence, production of pigments, pathogenicity, siderophore production, plasmid conjugal transfer, production of antibiotics and antifungal compounds and swarming [CITATION_1] .",
